# 🧪 Molecular Toxicity Classification Engine
## Master Project Roadmap — Tox21 Challenge (Final Version)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the authoritative, fully-updated roadmap. It supersedes the original 6-phase plan.
> All upgrades from the pipeline corrections, imbalance strategy, and literature review are integrated here.

---

## What This Project Actually Is

Not a toxicity classifier. A **Prediction-to-Prescription decision-support system** that:
1. Predicts toxicity across **all 12 Tox21 endpoints simultaneously**
2. Identifies **which molecular fragment** is responsible (SHAP × structural alert validation)
3. Suggests **synthesizable bioisostere replacements** (ChEMBL-backed, SAScore-filtered)
4. Re-predicts across **all 12 endpoints** for each candidate and outputs a **Pareto front**
5. Attaches **calibrated uncertainty intervals** and **OOD flags** to every prediction

**Closest prior art:** Cyto-Safe (Feitosa et al.) — which stops at step 2. You go through step 5.
**Key literature:** Zhang et al. (2025), Barua et al., Feitosa et al. (your extracted papers)

---

## Final Research Question

> **"Does SHAP-guided, structurally-validated, synthesizability-filtered bioisostere substitution produce consistent Pareto-dominant reductions across all 12 Tox21 toxicity endpoints for flagged compounds — and does the geometric cohesion of each endpoint's toxic class predict where SMOTE-augmented training and SHAP attribution systematically fail?"**

### Three Testable Claims
| # | Claim | How to Test |
|---|-------|-------------|
| 1 | SHAP × alert cross-validation is the first evaluation criterion for attribution quality in molecular toxicity | Overlap rate: SHAP high-confidence vs known toxic scaffolds |
| 2 | Pareto optimization reveals risk-shifting effects single-endpoint models miss | Show NR-AR↓ while SR-MMP↑ on real compounds |
| 3 | Geometric imbalance (intraclass Tanimoto cohesion) predicts SMOTE failure and SHAP attribution reliability | Correlate cohesion ratio with AUPRC gain from SMOTE across 12 endpoints |

---

## Architecture (Corrected)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["Input: SMILES String"] --> B["Phase 1: Environment + Data Acquisition"]
    B --> C["Phase 2: Multi-Representation Featurization\nECFP4/ECFP6/MACCS/RDKit ablation\n→ Scaffold-stratified split"]
    C --> D["Phase 3: Geometric Imbalance Analysis\n→ Intraclass Tanimoto cohesion per endpoint\n→ Focal Loss + per-endpoint weights\n→ SMOTE in embedding space (where valid)"]
    D --> E["Phase 4: ToxNet Training\nShared backbone + 12 task heads\nOPTUNA hyperparameter search\nMasked Focal Loss for NaN labels"]
    E --> F["Phase 5: Evaluation\nAUPRC primary, AUROC+F1+MCC secondary\nPer-endpoint threshold tuning (recall≥0.85)\nGeometric failure correlation"]
    F --> G["Phase 6: Prescription Pipeline\nSHAP → Alert validation → ChEMBL bioisostere\n→ SAScore filter → Pareto re-prediction\n→ OOD + uncertainty output"]
    G --> H["Phase 7: Dashboard\nPareto front UI + regulatory disclaimer"]
```

